comment: Johnson (BOS) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) shot attempt.

A player who falls while holding the ball or coming to a stop may not gain an advantage by sliding. RHH shows Middleton (MIL) gathers the ball with both feet on the floor. His feet then slide in opposite directions, providing no advantage before passing.
Thomas (BOS) wraps Middleton (MIL) around the waist.
Bayless (MIL) makes contact to Thomas's (BOS) body and affects his shot attempt.
Johnson (BOS) sets the screen on Middleton (MIL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bayless (MIL) dislodges Olynyk (BOS) as they engage under the rim for inbound pass.
Bradley (BOS) makes contact with Middleton's (MIL) arm on the shot attempt.
